    I searched various reviews and sizes/types of air fryers before purchasing this one. One of the things I reflected on prior to purchase was my kids. They are old enough to cook things themselves now when they want to, and a BIG thing for them is "Is it cooked yet, what does it now look like, what are you cooking in the air fryer". It is not enough for them to hear you answer they have to SEE IT and would constantly open the air fryer basket to see for themselves. This window solves all these problems!!Pros:Windows: visually see what is cooking, how it looks so far, without having to open the basket.Basket Lights: Useful for visual clarity as hard to see otherwise.Cleaning: Easy cleaning with the removeable trays, non stick too.Great size: Fits two slices of bread per basket (if that helps for size reference)Sync cooking: Now dinner can be done at once vs waiting for something that wasnt cooked yet.Cooking functions: Doesn't just air fry, it has bake, broil, reheat etc.Dual Baskets: Lets you cook two different items without trying to fit them in the same basket.Cons:Price -- more expensive if not on saleControls -- Because there is more options like SHAKE mode, preheat and various cooking settings, it can be a bit complex for some people at first. I needed to practice a few times before I got the hang of it and now have zero issues with it.Summary:  If you have a family and you have ever experienced them asking what you are cooking in the air fryer, or having to open the basket to check on your food, consider this WINDOW air fyer, it will be a game changer!!

