    Compatible with Voice Over but with a few quirks

Reviewed in Canada on August 1, 2025Style: Air FryerColour Name: WhiteSize: 4 QTVerified Purchase









    As a VoiceOver user, I was specifically looking for an air fryer with smart features that I could control with my iPhone. After a lot of research and contacting customer support, I found that this Cosori model, compatible with the VeSync app, is a great option.Pros:* Perfect VoiceOver Integration: The VeSync app on my iPhone syncs flawlessly with the air fryer. I can easily navigate the app with VoiceOver to manually set the time and temperature, or choose from a variety of presets like "Chicken Pro," "Fries Pro," "Vegetables," "Steak," and "Bacon Pro." I can also toggle the preheat function and the "Shake Reminder" on and off without any issues.* Convenient App Control: The ability to control the entire cooking process from my phone is a huge advantage. It's incredibly convenient to start, pause, and adjust settings without needing to be right next to the appliance.* Great Cooking Performance: The air fryer itself performs exceptionally well. I've made delicious and crispy fries without any added oil, cooked frozen steak perfectly, and gotten wonderfully crispy skin on chicken. It makes cooking these items a breeze.* Smart Home Compatibility: The product is indeed compatible with Alexa-enabled smart speakers, though this information was not easily accessible on the product page. I had to verify this with customer support.Cons & Areas for Improvement:* Inaccessible Display: The physical display on the unit is not readable with VoiceOver. I had to place a bump dot on the "power" and "start/pause" icons to be able to use the air fryer manually. While the app is fantastic, it would be much better if the physical unit's display were also accessible with tactile buttons.* Confusing Product Information: The Amazon product page and included documentation were very misleading. The product listing only says "smart" and does not specify compatibility with VoiceOver for iOS or TalkBack for Android. I had to contact customer support to confirm this feature.* Incorrect User Manual: The user manual provided with the unit was for a Phillips Oral-B toothbrush, and the user guide had no information about connecting to smart devices. This was frustrating and made setup more difficult than it needed to be.* Color-Specific Features: I was originally told by customer support that the smart features are only available on the white unit as indicated with the phone icone and Alexa icon on the product images..* Limited Cooking Functions: While it's great for fries, steak, and chicken, I would love to see more functions like baking and roasting for braised dishes with the other units.Summary:Despite the initial confusion with the product information and documentation, this is a fantastic air fryer for anyone who relies on VoiceOver. The seamless integration with the VeSync app makes cooking a far more accessible and enjoyable experience. The cooking results are excellent, and the added Alexa compatibility is a nice bonus. Cosori could significantly improve the user experience by making their product listings clearer, including the correct documentation, and making the physical display accessible. However, if you are a VoiceOver user looking for a smart air fryer, this is an excellent choice.

